    <description> # PDFCreator Server
Attention! This package installs software that requires a license.

## Features
- **PDFCreator Server** works as service and allows central management of settings and users.
- Share server printers in your network
- Auto-convert according to your settings without user interaction
- High performance due to the multi-threaded architecture
- The license fee is paid per server, not per user
- Like all PDFCreator Business solutions, this edition includes priority support by e-mail.

## Setup Command Line Parameters
To add command line parameters to the installer, please use:
`--installer-arguments="[parameters]"`

The list of possible `parameters` can be found below:
- **/LicenseKey=`LicenseKey`**
- **/ProxyUsername=`ProxyUsername`**
- **/ProxyPassword=`ProxyPassword`**
- **/ProxyName=`ProxyName`** - A port can also be specified with `ProxyName:Port`
- **/Lang="en"** - Two letter language code
- **/Dir="X:\DIR\PDFCreator"** - Absolute path to desired installation directory
- **/NoIcons** - No icons created on the Desktop
- **/DisableContextMenu** - No entries in the context menu
- **/DisableStartMenu** - No entries in the start menu
- **/DeferLicensingServiceStart** - Used to prevent the PDFCreator Licensing Service from activating the license automatically after the setup.
- **/ServiceUsername="User.Name"** - You can run the service as local system or use this to select a user
- **/ServicePassword="ABC1234!"** - Set the password that matches the username for the service

PDFCreator is a very lightweight application. If your machine is able to run a modern Windows OS without troubles, it should be able to run PDFCreator. For more detailed instructions please see the [user guide](https://docs.pdfforge.org/pdfcreator/en/pdfcreator/installing-pdfcreator/setup-command-line-parameters/)

